In article <1993Apr9.170824.1@tnclus.tele.nokia.fi> tarmoleinone@tnclus.tele.nokia.fi writes:
>        Is it a good or bad property for a hash function to
>        behave like following:
>
>        If the input and output widths contain equal amounts of
>        bits and the input is i and hash function is h(i) then
>        h(h(i))=i.


This violates my definition for a hash function -- namely that the function
not be invertible -- have no inversion in P (assuming P<>NP).

Are you using some other definition for "hash function"?


